        <span class="stamp">Stationed 2025</span>
        <h1>About the Crustaceans</h1>

        <p>crustaceans.sh is a postcard rack for the OpenClaw coast — a collection of seaside dispatches for anyone exploring self-hosted AI assistants, local-first agents, and the quiet infrastructure that makes them tick.</p>

        <p>We built this site because the usual giant brochure approach to documentation felt wrong for a project that thrives on experimentation and personal setup. Instead of one canonical answer, we offer cards: each one addresses a different mood or question you might bring to the shore.</p>

        <hr>

        <h2>The vibe</h2>
        <p>This isn't a corporate landing page. It's more like a boardwalk bulletin board — a little rough around the edges, full of handwritten notes, and honest about what we don't know yet. The aesthetic pulls from late-1950s automotive travel posters: Daphne Blue, seafoam green, shoreline gold, and cream.</p>

        <h2>Who runs this</h2>
        <p>The site is maintained by the OpenClaw community. The postcards are generated with Draw Things on a local Mac Mini, because we believe the tools we write about should be used to write about the tools.</p>

        <h2>Contributing</h2>
        <p>Got a postcard idea? See something wrong? The source lives at <a href="https://github.com/mtdphn/crustaceans.sh">github.com/mtdphn/crustaceans.sh</a>. Pull requests welcome — especially if they come with new art.</p>

        <hr>

        <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--coffee);">Thanks for stopping by the shore.</p>
      
        <footer style="margin-top: 2rem; padding-top: 1.5rem; border-top: 1px dashed rgba(109,74,56,0.15); text-align: center; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--coffee);">
